          <h2 style="font-size:20px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">Afghan-Pakistan tensions</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Pakistan's military launched <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-27-dec-2024-6-air-raids" target="_blank">air raids</a> inside Afghanistan's Paktika province on Tuesday night, targeting Pakistan Taliban, <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-27-dec-2024-7-tehrik-e-taliban-pakistan" target="_blank">Tehrik-e Taliban Pakistan</a>, hideouts. The Taliban-led Afghan government condemned the strikes, claiming at least 46 civilians, including women and children, were killed, and vowed retaliation. These air raids follow a surge in TTP attacks on Pakistani security forces.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Pakistan has been accusing the Afghan Taliban of harboring TTP fighters, which is a claim that Kabul denies. The airstrikes are part of Pakistan's broader military campaign aimed at curbing TTP cross-border operations. Experts fear and warn that these measures demonstrate the lack of a consistent strategy, further complicating Pakistan-Afghanistan relations and raising the risk of further retaliation from the PTT or the Afghan government.</p>
        </mj-text>
