          Japanese Foreign Minister Takeshi Iwaya voiced <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-27-dec-2024-8-serious-concerns" target="_blank">serious concerns</a> over China's military buildup during a Christmas meeting with his Chinese counterpart Wang Yi in Beijing. He highlighted issues around the East China Sea, particularly near the disputed Senkaku Islands, and criticized China's anti-espionage laws. The ministers did talk about stabilizing ties with plans for Wang to visit Japan next year. Both nations have tensions over territorial disputes, military activities, and historical grievances. Despite this, they pledged to put forth an effort toward a "constructive and stable" relationship.</p>
