          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;"><strong>🇰🇷 South Korea:</strong>   
          Just weeks after President Yoon Suk Yeol was impeached, South Korea's opposition lawmakers voted to <a href="https://www.dw.com/en/south-korea-lawmakers-vote-to-impeach-han-duck-soo/a-71166862" target="_blank">impeach</a> Prime Minister and acting President Han Duck-soo. Han is accused of obstructing opposition-nominated constitutional court appointments and vetoing investigations into Yoon's short-lived martial law declaration. The opposing Democratic Party of Korea has the majority in the parliament. The impeachment motion needed 151 out of 300 MPs to vote for it. It passed with 192 votes.</p>
