          <h2 style="font-size:20px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">How did Slovenia become independent?</h2>
        </mj-text>
         <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/gp-dec-27-3.jpg" alt="foundations" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
           <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Slovenia celebrates its <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-27-dec-2024-10-independence-and-unity-day" target="_blank">Independence and Unity Day</a> on December 26. Although the country officially declared independence in June 1991, it uses this date based on the 1990 independence referendum results. The referendum was held because of growing political differences with the rest of Yugoslavia on the future direction of the federal state as well as the deteriorating economic situation. After a <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-27-dec-2024-11-95-majority" target="_blank">95% majority</a> voted in favor of independence, the country declared independence six months after it failed a negotiation with other Yugoslav republics to form a loose confederation.​</p>
           <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Slovenia was the first Yugoslav nation to declare “sovereignty” in 1990, using the logic that Slovenian law took precedence over Yugoslav law. While it had a ten-day war after the Declaration of Independence, its path was much more peaceful than Croatia's or Bosnia’s. Slovenia managed to avoid many of the damaging effects of the Balkan War. They were also the first country from former Yugoslavia to join the EU. As the nation celebrates 33 years of its break up from the Socialist Federal Republic of Yugoslavia, there is still an element of <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-27-dec-2024-12-yugonostalgia" target="_blank">Yugonostalgia</a> that can be found today in Slovenia.​</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
